alert.note: Alert for Coastal Levy; Inland Levy (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Watch issued June 23 at 4:45AM EDT until June 23 at 8:00AM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay
info.description: .Moisture streaming into the Florida peninsula from the Gulf of Mexico will lead to multiple rounds of heavy rainfall through today. ...FLOOD WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT THROUGH THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues to be possible. * WHERE...A portion of west central Florida, including the following areas, Coastal Levy and Inland Levy. * WHEN...Through this evening. * IMPACTS...Excessive runoff may result in flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 3 inches is forecast today, with locally higher totals possible. These rainfall amounts over saturated soil conditions may lead to flooding. - https://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible Flood Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be prepared to take action should flooding develop.
